# The committed sample dataset (docs/samples/, DATA-SPEC §9.5) is compared
# byte-for-byte against a fresh build by the I16 drift guard, so Git must not
# rewrite it on the way in or out of the working tree.
#
# Only the CSVs need pinning. `csv.writer` terminates rows with a literal CRLF
# on every platform (RFC 4180), so those bytes are already in the blob; on a
# Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true — the GitHub runner default — Git
# would smudge each LF again and hand the guard \r\r\n. The .json and .md
# samples are written through Python text mode, which emits the platform's own
# line ending, so they must keep travelling as ordinary text and match whatever
# the machine running the guard produces.
docs/samples/**/*.csv -text
